            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Isler suggests reading Antallos in line 1. It is very plausible that IGPalermo 40 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001560">ISic001560</ref>, found at Monte Iato in 1969, constitutes part of the same inscription (Isler 2000 argues for the association), but without autopsy of the piece and proper comparison with these two fragments we continue to treat it as a distinct fragment for now.</p>
            </div>
